==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin [[zona]] < Greek [[ζώνη]] (''z&#333;n&#275;'', '[[girdle]],' '[[belt]]').

===Pronunciation===
*zōn, /zəʊn/, /<tt>z@Un</tt>/

===Noun===
'''zone''' (''plural:'' [[zones]])

# An area distinguished on the basis of a particular characteristic, use, restriction, etc.
#{{baseball}} The [[strike zone]].

